      <hedline>
        <hl1>Voter-Friendly Elections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Charles Brand letter favors direct election of president and amending Constitution to allow voting over two days</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>A Sept. 27 letter is right to argue that our electoral vote system should be replaced by direct election of the president. But that does not go far enough. The Constitution should be amended so that voting would occur on a weekend, perhaps over two days, and end at the same hour nationwide.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>A Sept. 27 letter is right to argue that our electoral vote system should be replaced by direct election of the president. But that does not go far enough. The Constitution should be amended so that voting would occur on a weekend, perhaps over two days, and end at the same hour nationwide.</p>
        <p>This would avoid disfranchising those whose work or family obligations make voting on a Tuesday difficult. Also, results from the East Coast would not be known until voting in the West had ended.</p>
        <p>CHARLES BRAND  New York, Sept. 27, 2000</p>
      </block>
